{"title_page": "Drone (2014 film)", "text_new": ":''Not to be confused with [[Drones (2013 film)]], an American thriller film.''\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Drone\n| image          = Drone 2014 film poster.jpg\n| alt            = In a desert landscape, a Middle Eastern boy points a slingshot at an unmanned aerial vehicle flying above the clouds.\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Tonje Hessen Schei]]\n| producer       = Lars L\u00f8ge\n| writer         = <!-- or: | writers = -->\n| starring       = \n| narrator       = <!-- or: | narrators = -->\n| music          = Olav \u00d8yehaug\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist |\n* Steven Moore\n* Anna Myking\n}}\n| editing        = Joakim Schager\n| studio         = Flimmer Film\n| distributor    = <!-- or: | distributors = -->\n| released       = {{film date|2014|04|15|[[Arte]]|2015|02|27|Norway}}\n| runtime        = {{Plainlist |\n* 58 minutes <small>(TV edit)</small>\n* 79 minutes <small>(theatrical edit)</small>\n}}\n| country        = Norway\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = <!--(please use condensed and rounded values, e.g. \"\u00a311.6 million\" not \"\u00a311,586,221\")-->\n}}\n'''''Drone''''' is a 2014 English-language documentary film directed by Norwegian director [[Tonje Hessen Schei]]. The film explores the use of [[Unmanned combat aerial vehicle|drones in warfare]]. ''Drone'' aired on the TV network [[Arte]] on {{nowrap|April 15}}, 2014. The documentary screened at several film festivals throughout 2014, winning several awards. ''Drone'' was released in Norway on {{nowrap|February 27}}, 2015.\n\n==Premise==\n\n''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' reported, \"'Drone' depicts the recruitment of young pilots at gaming conventions, explores the changing perceptions of what 'going to war' means, as well as the moral stance of engineers behind the technology. The docu also investigates the ways in which world leaders engage in wars, as well as look at the struggle of anti-war and civil rights activists.\"<ref name=\"keslassy\" />\n\n==Production==\n\n''Drone'' was produced by Lars L\u00f8ge at Flimmer Film and directed by Tonje Hessen Schei. The film received financial support from backers in Norway and from around the world.<ref name=\"keslassy\">{{cite journal | last=Keslassy | first=Elsa | url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/levelk-unleashes-drone-at-goteborg-exclusive-1201077991/ | title=LevelK Unleashes \u2018Drone\u2019 At Goteborg | journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | date=January 30, 2014 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213211835/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/levelk-unleashes-drone-at-goteborg-exclusive-1201077991/# | archive-date=2015-02-13 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n\n===Theatrical screenings===\nThe sales outfit LevelK acquired ''Drone'' at the Nordic Film Market at the [[Gothenburg Film Festival]] in January 2014.<ref name=\"keslassy\" /> A 58-minute cut of ''Drone'' premiered on the TV network [[Arte]] on {{nowrap|April 15}}, 2014.<ref>{{cite news | last=Woods | first=Chris | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/14/cia-drones-pakistan-us-air-force-documentary | title=CIA's Pakistan drone strikes carried out by regular US air force personnel | work=[[The Guardian]] | date=April 14, 2014 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150217182529/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/14/cia-drones-pakistan-us-air-force-documentary# | archive-date=2015-02-17 | url-status=live }}</ref> A 79-minute cut was edited for subsequent screenings.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.levelk.dk/Default/film?id=116 | title=Drone | work=levelk.dk | publisher=LevelK | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929114636/http://www.levelk.dk/Default/film?id=116# | archive-date=2014-09-29 | url-status=live }}</ref> In October 2014, ''Drone'' screened at the [[Bergen International Film Festival]] and won Best Norwegian Documentary and the Checkpoint Human Rights awards. In January 2015, it screened at the [[Troms\u00f8 International Film Festival]] and won the Norwegian Peace Film Award. In the following February, it screened at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]] and won the [[Cinema for Peace]] award. In the same month, LevelK sold distribution rights to ''Drone'' to several major territories.<ref>{{cite news | author=Staff | url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/distribution/drone-flies-for-levelk/5083201.article | title=Drone flies for LevelK | work=Screen Daily | date=February 12, 2015 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150322055757/http://www.screendaily.com/news/distribution/drone-flies-for-levelk/5083201.article# | archive-date=2015-03-22 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n''Drone'' was released in Norway on {{nowrap|February 27}}, 2015.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dronethedocumentary.com/ | title=Drone | work=dronethedocumentary.com | publisher=LevelK | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213210218/http://www.dronethedocumentary.com/ | archive-date=February 13, 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref> It was released in the United Kingdom on {{nowrap|April 10}}, 2015.<ref>{{cite news | last=De Semlyen | first=Phil | url=http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=43781 | title=Exclusive Clip From Drone | work=[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]] | date=March 24, 2015 | accessdate=March 25, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402131848/http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=43781# | archive-date=2015-04-02 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\n\nJohn DeFore, reviewing for ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', called ''Drone'' \"an important contribution to debates over a means of warfare that is just in its infancy\". DeFore said the documentary had an \"effective and clear-headed\" presentation of \"multiple sides of the debate\". The critic concluded, \"''Drone'' takes a quick look at realities of the warfare industry and asks the obvious question: How will Americans feel when another government (or non-governmental entity) has remote-controlled death hovering constantly over ''our'' heads?\"<ref>{{cite journal | last=DeFore | first=John | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/drone-bergen-review-737540 | title='Drone': Bergen Review | journal=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date=October 2, 2014 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216005955/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/drone-bergen-review-737540# | archive-date=2015-02-16 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[List of films featuring drones]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|http://www.dronethedocumentary.com/}}\n*{{IMDb title|3801730|Drone}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.democracynow.org/2015/11/20/exclusive_2_air_force_vets_speak |title=Exclusive: 2 Air Force Vets Speak Out for First Time on Why They Want the Drone War to Stop  |accessdate= }} - an interview with those in the documentary at ''[[Democracy Now!]]''\n\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:Norwegian documentary films]]\n[[Category:Norwegian films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about military aviation]]\n[[Category:Unmanned military aircraft]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about robots]]\n", "text_old": ":''Not to be confused with [[Drones (2013 film)]], an American thriller film.''\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Drone\n| image          = Drone 2014 film poster.jpg\n| alt            = In a desert landscape, a Middle Eastern boy points a slingshot at an unmanned aerial vehicle flying above the clouds.\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = Tonje Hessen Schei\n| producer       = Lars L\u00f8ge\n| writer         = <!-- or: | writers = -->\n| starring       = \n| narrator       = <!-- or: | narrators = -->\n| music          = Olav \u00d8yehaug\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist |\n* Steven Moore\n* Anna Myking\n}}\n| editing        = Joakim Schager\n| studio         = Flimmer Film\n| distributor    = <!-- or: | distributors = -->\n| released       = {{film date|2014|04|15|[[Arte]]|2015|02|27|Norway}}\n| runtime        = {{Plainlist |\n* 58 minutes <small>(TV edit)</small>\n* 79 minutes <small>(theatrical edit)</small>\n}}\n| country        = Norway\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = <!--(please use condensed and rounded values, e.g. \"\u00a311.6 million\" not \"\u00a311,586,221\")-->\n}}\n'''''Drone''''' is a 2014 English-language documentary film directed by Norwegian director Tonje Hessen Schei. The film explores the use of [[Unmanned combat aerial vehicle|drones in warfare]]. ''Drone'' aired on the TV network [[Arte]] on {{nowrap|April 15}}, 2014. The documentary screened at several film festivals throughout 2014, winning several awards. ''Drone'' was released in Norway on {{nowrap|February 27}}, 2015.\n\n==Premise==\n\n''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' reported, \"'Drone' depicts the recruitment of young pilots at gaming conventions, explores the changing perceptions of what 'going to war' means, as well as the moral stance of engineers behind the technology. The docu also investigates the ways in which world leaders engage in wars, as well as look at the struggle of anti-war and civil rights activists.\"<ref name=\"keslassy\" />\n\n==Production==\n\n''Drone'' was produced by Lars L\u00f8ge at Flimmer Film and directed by Tonje Hessen Schei. The film received financial support from backers in Norway and from around the world.<ref name=\"keslassy\">{{cite journal | last=Keslassy | first=Elsa | url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/levelk-unleashes-drone-at-goteborg-exclusive-1201077991/ | title=LevelK Unleashes \u2018Drone\u2019 At Goteborg | journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | date=January 30, 2014 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213211835/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/levelk-unleashes-drone-at-goteborg-exclusive-1201077991/# | archive-date=2015-02-13 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n\n===Theatrical screenings===\nThe sales outfit LevelK acquired ''Drone'' at the Nordic Film Market at the [[Gothenburg Film Festival]] in January 2014.<ref name=\"keslassy\" /> A 58-minute cut of ''Drone'' premiered on the TV network [[Arte]] on {{nowrap|April 15}}, 2014.<ref>{{cite news | last=Woods | first=Chris | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/14/cia-drones-pakistan-us-air-force-documentary | title=CIA's Pakistan drone strikes carried out by regular US air force personnel | work=[[The Guardian]] | date=April 14, 2014 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150217182529/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/14/cia-drones-pakistan-us-air-force-documentary# | archive-date=2015-02-17 | url-status=live }}</ref> A 79-minute cut was edited for subsequent screenings.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.levelk.dk/Default/film?id=116 | title=Drone | work=levelk.dk | publisher=LevelK | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929114636/http://www.levelk.dk/Default/film?id=116# | archive-date=2014-09-29 | url-status=live }}</ref> In October 2014, ''Drone'' screened at the [[Bergen International Film Festival]] and won Best Norwegian Documentary and the Checkpoint Human Rights awards. In January 2015, it screened at the [[Troms\u00f8 International Film Festival]] and won the Norwegian Peace Film Award. In the following February, it screened at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]] and won the [[Cinema for Peace]] award. In the same month, LevelK sold distribution rights to ''Drone'' to several major territories.<ref>{{cite news | author=Staff | url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/distribution/drone-flies-for-levelk/5083201.article | title=Drone flies for LevelK | work=Screen Daily | date=February 12, 2015 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150322055757/http://www.screendaily.com/news/distribution/drone-flies-for-levelk/5083201.article# | archive-date=2015-03-22 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n''Drone'' was released in Norway on {{nowrap|February 27}}, 2015.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dronethedocumentary.com/ | title=Drone | work=dronethedocumentary.com | publisher=LevelK | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213210218/http://www.dronethedocumentary.com/ | archive-date=February 13, 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref> It was released in the United Kingdom on {{nowrap|April 10}}, 2015.<ref>{{cite news | last=De Semlyen | first=Phil | url=http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=43781 | title=Exclusive Clip From Drone | work=[[Empire (magazine)|Empire]] | date=March 24, 2015 | accessdate=March 25, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402131848/http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=43781# | archive-date=2015-04-02 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\n\nJohn DeFore, reviewing for ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', called ''Drone'' \"an important contribution to debates over a means of warfare that is just in its infancy\". DeFore said the documentary had an \"effective and clear-headed\" presentation of \"multiple sides of the debate\". The critic concluded, \"''Drone'' takes a quick look at realities of the warfare industry and asks the obvious question: How will Americans feel when another government (or non-governmental entity) has remote-controlled death hovering constantly over ''our'' heads?\"<ref>{{cite journal | last=DeFore | first=John | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/drone-bergen-review-737540 | title='Drone': Bergen Review | journal=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date=October 2, 2014 | accessdate=February 13, 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216005955/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/drone-bergen-review-737540# | archive-date=2015-02-16 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[List of films featuring drones]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|http://www.dronethedocumentary.com/}}\n*{{IMDb title|3801730|Drone}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.democracynow.org/2015/11/20/exclusive_2_air_force_vets_speak |title=Exclusive: 2 Air Force Vets Speak Out for First Time on Why They Want the Drone War to Stop  |accessdate= }} - an interview with those in the documentary at ''[[Democracy Now!]]''\n\n[[Category:2010s documentary films]]\n[[Category:Norwegian documentary films]]\n[[Category:Norwegian films]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about military aviation]]\n[[Category:Unmanned military aircraft]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about robots]]\n", "name_user": "Geysirhead", "label": "safe", "comment": "added link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drone_(2014_film)"}
