Kingdom of the Netherlands)|Suriname]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] former professional [[football (soccer)|footballer]].\n\nVerveer has played his football across several countries including [[Netherlands]], [[Switzerland]], [[England]], [[Scotland]] and [[Italy]].\n\n==External links==\n{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Verveer, Etienne}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Paramaribo]]\n[[Category:Surinamese emigrants to the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Dutch footballers]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Millwall F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Aberdeen F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:S.S. Ischia Isolaverde players]]\n\n\n{{Netherlands-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up, remove unref height", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Etienne_Verveer"}
{"title_page": "Michael Forever \u2013 The Tribute Concert", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox music festival\n| music_festival_name = Michael Forever - The Tribute Concert. \n| image               = [[File:Michael Jackson Tribute Concert Logo.jpg|230px]]\n| caption             = \n| location            = [[Millennium Stadium]] in [[Cardiff]], [[Wales]], United Kingdom\n| years_active        = 2011\n| founders            = [[Katherine Jackson]]\n| dates               = Saturday 8 October 2011\n| genre               = [[Benefit concert]]\n| website             = [http://www.michaelforevertribute.com www.michaelforevertribute.com]\n}}\n\n'''Michael Forever \u2013 The Tribute Concert''' was a [[music concert|music]] [[benefit concert]] which was held on 8 October 2011 at the 74,500 seater [[Millennium Stadium]] in [[Cardiff]], the capital of [[Wales]].\n\nThe concert was dedicated to American entertainer [[Michael Jackson]], who [[Death of Michael Jackson|died]] on 25 June 2009 after suffering a [[cardiac arrest]], and celebrated the 40th anniversary of his solo career.<ref name=\"guardian\">{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/aug/12/michael-jackson-tribute-concert-lineup |title= Michael Jackson tribute concert lineup revealed |publisher= Guardian |accessdate=12 August 2011 |location=London |first=Sean |last=Michaels |date=12 August 2011}}</ref> The concert helped to raise awareness and funds for [[AIDS Project Los Angeles]] and [[The Prince's Trust]].<ref name=\"BBC1\">{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-14502151 |title= Christina Aguilera to play Jackson concert |publisher= BBC News |accessdate=12 August 2011 |date=12 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe event was already in \"advanced stages\" in April 2011, when it was presented to the majority of the Jackson family. Katherine Jackson said \"Michael gave his entire life to the world through his love, his music and his devotion to healing the planet. I am positive that this event will be an event great enough in scale, talent and imagination to form a worthy celebration of Michael's life.\"<ref name=\"guardian2\"/>\n\n==Production and broadcasters==\nThe concert was organised by Global Live Events [[Limited liability partnership|LLP]], formed by film producers Michael Henry and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] Chris Hunt, and US CEO [[Eric Bute]].<ref name=\"guardian2\">{{cite web|url= http://www.globalliveeventsuk.com/category/leadership|publisher= Global Live Events|title= Leadership|accessdate= 7 August 2011|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://archive.is/20111007130556/http://www.globalliveeventsuk.com/category/leadership|archivedate= 7 October 2011|df= dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIt was expected that the concert would be broadcast throughout the world to 30 countries in [[Standard-definition television|2D]] and [[3D television|3D]] formats. However, this was later cancelled due to copyright issues.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/jul/26/michael-jackson-tribute-concert-wales|publisher= [[guardian.co.uk]] |title= Family divided over plans for Michael Jackson tribute concert in Wales |accessdate=7 August 2011 |location=London |first=Ben |last=Quinn |date=26 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Ticket pricing and ticket sales==\nTickets were priced from [[GBP|\u00a3]]55. Standard seats cost \u00a387, with a restricted view at \u00a355. Standard middle and upper-tier tickets cost \u00a3175 and \u00a3137 respectively and the more restricted standing tickets were sold at \u00a397. The best seats in the middle tier were priced at \u00a3240 each, while the best standing tickets cost \u00a3195.<ref name=\"tickets\">{{cite web|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2011/08/12/line-up-for-cardiff-s-michael-jackson-tribute-concert-revealed-at-last-91466-29222230/#ixzz1VBpZndfH |title= Line-up for Cardiff's Michael Jackson tribute concert revealed at last |publisher= [[CardiffOnline]] |accessdate=12 August 2011}}</ref> Student tickets were available from \u00a325.<ref name=\"studenttickets\">{{cite web |url= http://www.totalstudents.co.uk/event.php?eid=54011 |title= Student Tickets for Michael Jackson tribute concert |publisher= Total Students |accessdate= 29 September 2011 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20111005164612/http://www.totalstudents.co.uk/event.php?eid=54011 |archivedate= 5 October 2011 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nChris Hunt of Global Live Events confirmed before the event that the stadium's capacity had been reduced down from 75,000 to 50,000, with only 40,000 tickets having been sold.<ref name=\"Hunt\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-15217272|title= Michael Jackson concert: 40,000 tribute tickets sold|publisher= [[BBC]] |accessdate=10 April 2012|date=7 October 2011}}</ref> [[Cardiff Council]] also confirmed that some council staff and councillors were sent e-mails by the Millennium Stadium offering them \"a number of free tickets\" to the event. A Cardiff Council spokesperson confirmed that they did not know how many free tickets were available, but they were not offered to all council staff.<ref name=\"council\">{{cite web|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/2011/10/08/cardiff-left-star-struck-by-jackson-gig-performers-91466-29559243/#ixzz1raouWyqW |title= Cardiff left star struck by Jackson gig performers|publisher= [[CardiffOnline]] |accessdate=10 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Support==\nThe event was organised by Global Live Events and had the support of Jackson's mother [[Katherine Jackson]],<ref name=\"tickets\"/> his sister [[La Toya Jackson|La Toya]] and his brothers [[Tito Jackson|Tito]], [[Marlon Jackson|Marlon]] and [[Jackie Jackson|Jackie]], but not that of his other brothers [[Randy Jackson|Randy]] and [[Jermaine Jackson|Jermaine]], his other sister [[Janet Jackson|Janet]], several relatives, the official Michael Jackson Fan Club or even the singer's executors, as they claimed the concert would distract from the involuntary manslaughter trial of Dr. [[Conrad Murray]], Jackson's former doctor. Randy and Jermaine issued the following statement in opposition to the event:\n\n<blockquote>While we wholeheartedly support the spirit of a tribute that honours our brother, we find it impossible to support an event that is due to take place during the criminal trial surrounding Michael's death. As everyone knows, those proceedings commence 20 September, and this Michael Forever concert takes place in Cardiff, Wales, on 8 October. In light of this, we feel it is inappropriate to be involved with such an ill-timed event and its promoter, Global Live. Furthermore, the decision to proceed with this concert disrespects opinions and wishes expressed in the strongest terms to Global Live during conversations in April when this event was presented to the majority of the family as an idea already in its advanced stages. There will come a time and place for an amazing and deserving tribute to Michael. But we feel that the most important tribute we can give to our brother at this time is to seek justice in his name.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-14287845 |publisher= [[BBC]] |title= Michael Jackson Cardiff show: Brothers criticise timing|accessdate=7 August 2011 |date=26 July 2011}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nThe Michael Jackson Fan Club agreed with the two brothers, issuing a similar statement:\n\n<blockquote>\"We share their concerns that this concert is taking place at a most inappropriate time when everyone's care and attention should be focused on the matter of justice. We believe that, as stated by Jermaine and Randy, the most important tribute we can give to Michael Jackson at this time is to seek justice in his name.\"<ref name=\"MJFC\">{{cite web |url= http://mjfanclub.net/home/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4721:statement-from-mjfc&catid=85:latest-news&Itemid=82 |publisher= MJFC |title= Statement From MJFC|accessdate=7 August 2011}}</ref>\n</blockquote>\n\n==Performing acts==\nMusical acts who participated in the event included the [[The Jacksons|Jackson Brothers]], [[Christina Aguilera]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Beyonc\u00e9]], [[Alexandra Burke]], [[Yolanda Adams]], [[3T]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Alien Ant Farm]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Cee Lo Green]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Pixie Lott]], [[Diversity (dance troupe)|Diversity]], [[Craig David]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[JLS]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Ne-Yo]], [[Jamie Foxx]], [[Gladys Knight]], [[La Toya Jackson]], [[Leona Lewis]]<ref name=\"BBC1\"/> and [[Smokey Robinson]].<ref name=\"BBC1\"/> The [[BBC Radio 1]] presenter [[Fearne Cotton]] co-hosted the event with [[Jamie Foxx]].<ref name=\"Hunt\"/>\n\nIn the days running up to the event, three of the acts originally booked to perform pulled out: [[The Black Eyed Peas]], due to \"unforeseeable circumstances\", which led to speculation in the media that the band were splitting up; [[Chris Brown]], who failed to enter the country for the event as his working visa was denied over the assault of former girlfriend [[Rihanna]]; and [[Jennifer Hudson]], due to \"production issues\". [[Kiss (band)|KISS]] was also removed from the lineup after bass guitarist Gene Simmons made some hurtful comments against Jackson based on the child molestation allegations.\n\n===Setlist===\n\n# [[Rollercoaster]]\n# [[dgjyaefgdklv \u00f1pcfhsglv\u00f1\u00b4j,]] - [[JLS]]\n# [[Blame It on the Boogie]] - JLS & The Jacksons\n# [[Shake Your Body (Down to the Ground)]] - [[The Jacksons]]\n# [[Rock with You]] - [[Jamie Foxx]]\n# [[Smooth Criminal]]\n# [[P.Y.T. (Pretty Young Thing)]] - [[Alien Ant Farm]]\n# [[Stranger in Moscow]]\n# [[I'll Be There (The Jackson 5 song)|I'll Be There]] - [[Leona Lewis]]\n# [[Human Nature (Michael Jackson song)|Human Nature]] - [[Craig David]]\n# [[Can You Feel It (The Jacksons song)|Can You Feel It]]/[[Show You the Way to Go]]/[[Smooth Criminal]]/[[Dangerous (Michael Jackson album)|Dangerous]]/[[Thriller (Michael Jackson album)|Thriller]] - Dance Jam\n# [[She's Out of My Life]] - [[Smokey Robinson]]\n# Believe in Yourself - [[Gladys Knight]]\n# [[I Wanna Be Where You Are]] - [[Beyonc\u00e9]] (On Video Screen)\n# [[I Just Can't Stop Loving You]] - Gladys Knight & Smokey Robinson\n# [[Why (3T song)|Why]]/[[Heartbreak Hotel]] - 3T & [[Tito Jackson]]\n# [[Jam (song)|Jam]]/[[Black or White]]/[[Remember the Time]]/[[Behind the Mask (Michael Jackson song)|Behind the Mask]] - [[Diversity (dance troupe)|Diversity]]\n# [[In the Closet]]/[[Jam (song)|Jam]] - [[La Toya Jackson]]\n# [[I Can't Help It (Michael Jackson song)|I Can't Help It]]\n# [[You Can't Win (song)|You Can't Win]] - [[Cee Lo Green]]\n# Smile\n# [[Dirty Diana]] - [[Christina Aguilera]]\n# [[I Want You Back]]\n# [[You Are Not Alone]] - [[Pixie Lott]]\n# [[Earth Song]] \n# [[Another Part of Me]] - [[Yolanda Adams]]\n# [[Who's Loving You]]\n# [[Scream/Childhood|Scream]] - [[Alexandra Burke]]\n# [[Leave Me Alone (Michael Jackson song)|Leave Me Alone]]\n# [[Gone Too Soon]] - [[Jennifer Hudson]]\n# [[Don't Stop 'Til You Get Enough]] - Jamie Foxx, JLS & The Jacksons\n\n==Aftermath of the event==\nGlobal Live Events LLP, which had been formed on 29 March 2011 by film producers Michael Henry and Chris Hunt went into [[Administration (law)|administration]] on the day of the concert, when both Henry and Hunt both quit the partnership.<ref name=Administration>{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/nov/29/michael-jackson-tribute-concert-company-bust|publisher= [[guardian.co.uk]]|title= Michael Jackson tribute concert company goes bust|accessdate=27 December 2011|location=London|first=Sean|last=Michaels|date=29 November 2011}}</ref>\nBoth men, Global Live Events and Hunt's media company Iambic Productions were sued in the High Court by Quickdraw - a private investment fund, over ownership of the recordings of the concert. Quickdraw won the case, with the judge stating that Hunt and Henry were 'the most unreliable of witnesses' and their account to the court was 'wholly unbelievable'. Quickdraw was awarded damages of \u00a35 million and costs of in excess of \u00a3700,000\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of music concerts at the Millennium Stadium]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20111029153612/http://home.michaelforevertribute.com/home.html Official website]\n* [http://www.facebook.com/M4Tribute Official Facebook Page]\n* [https://twitter.com/M4Tribute Official Twitter Page]\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-14289473 Video of Concert Announcement from BBC News]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20111005164612/http://www.totalstudents.co.uk/event.php?eid=54011 Link for \u00a325 Student Tickets]\n\n{{Michael Jackson}}\n{{Culture in Cardiff}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Michael Forever - The Tribute Concert}}\n[[Category:Benefit concerts in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Michael Jackson]]\n[[Category:Tribute concerts in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2011 in Wales]]\n[[Category:2011 in music]]\n[[Category:Events in Cardiff]]\n[[Category:Millennium Stadium]]\n[[Category:2010s in Cardiff]]\n[[Category:October 2011 events in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox music festival\n| music_festival_name = Michael Forever - The Tribute Concert. \n| image               = [[File:Michael Jackson Tribute Concert Logo.jpg|230px]]\n| caption             = \n| location            = [[Millennium Stadium]] in [[Cardiff]], [[Wales]], United Kingdom\n| years_active        = 2011\n| founders            = [[Katherine Jackson]]\n| dates               = Saturday 8 October 2011\n| genre               = [[Benefit concert]]\n| website             = [http://www.michaelforevertribute.com www.michaelforevertribute.com]\n}}\n\n'''Michael Forever \u2013 The Tribute Concert''' was a [[music concert|music]] [[benefit concert]] which was held on 8 October 2011 at the 74,500 seater [[Millennium Stadium]] in [[Cardiff]], the capital of [[Wales]].\n\nThe concert was dedicated to American entertainer [[Michael Jackson]], who [[Death of Michael Jackson|died]] on 25 June 2009 after suffering a [[cardiac arrest]], and celebrated the 40th anniversary of his solo career.<ref name=\"guardian\">{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/aug/12/michael-jackson-tribute-concert-lineup |title= Michael Jackson tribute concert lineup revealed |publisher= Guardian |accessdate=12 August 2011 |location=London |first=Sean |last=Michaels |date=12 August 2011}}</ref> The concert helped to raise awareness and funds for [[AIDS Project Los Angeles]] and [[The Prince's Trust]].<ref name=\"BBC1\">{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-14502151 |title= Christina Aguilera to play Jackson concert |publisher= BBC News |accessdate=12 August 2011 |date=12 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe event was already in \"advanced stages\" in April 2011, when it was presented to the majority of the Jackson family. Katherine Jackson said \"Michael gave his entire life to the world through his love, his music and his devotion to healing the planet. I am positive that this event will be an event great enough in scale, talent and imagination to form a worthy celebration of Michael's life.\"<ref name=\"guardian2\"/>\n\n==Production and broadcasters==\nThe concert was organised by Global Live Events [[Limited liability partnership|LLP]], formed by film producers Michael Henry and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] Chris Hunt, and US CEO [[Eric Bute]].<ref name=\"guardian2\">{{cite web|url= http://www.globalliveeventsuk.com/category/leadership|publisher= Global Live Events|title= Leadership|accessdate= 7 August 2011|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://archive.is/20111007130556/http://www.globalliveeventsuk.com/category/leadership|archivedate= 7 October 2011|df= dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIt was expected that the concert would be broadcast throughout the world to 30 countries in [[Standard-definition television|2D]] and [[3D television|3D]] formats. However, this was later cancelled due to copyright issues.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/jul/26/michael-jackson-tribute-concert-wales|publisher= [[guardian.co.uk]] |title= Family divided over plans for Michael Jackson tribute concert in Wales |accessdate=7 August 2011 |location=London |first=Ben |last=Quinn |date=26 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Ticket pricing and ticket sales==\nTickets were priced from [[GBP|\u00a3]]55. Standard seats cost \u00a387, with a restricted view at \u00a355. Standard middle and upper-tier tickets cost \u00a3175 and \u00a3137 respectively and the more restricted standing tickets were sold at \u00a397. The best seats in the middle tier were priced at \u00a3240 each, while the best standing tickets cost \u00a3195.<ref name=\"tickets\">{{cite web|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2011/08/12/line-up-for-cardiff-s-michael-jackson-tribute-concert-revealed-at-last-91466-29222230/#ixzz1VBpZndfH |title= Line-up for Cardiff's Michael Jackson tribute concert revealed at last |publisher= [[CardiffOnline]] |accessdate=12 August 2011}}</ref> Student tickets were available from \u00a325.<ref name=\"studenttickets\">{{cite web |url= http://www.totalstudents.co.uk/event.php?eid=54011 |title= Student Tickets for Michael Jackson tribute concert |publisher= Total Students |accessdate= 29 September 2011 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20111005164612/http://www.totalstudents.co.uk/event.php?eid=54011 |archivedate= 5 October 2011 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nChris Hunt of Global Live Events confirmed before the event that the stadium's capacity had been reduced down from 75,000 to 50,000, with only 40,000 tickets having been sold.<ref name=\"Hunt\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-15217272|title= Michael Jackson concert: 40,000 tribute tickets sold|publisher= [[BBC]] |accessdate=10 April 2012|date=7 October 2011}}</ref> [[Cardiff Council]] also confirmed that some council staff and councillors were sent e-mails by the Millennium Stadium offering them \"a number of free tickets\" to the event. A Cardiff Council spokesperson confirmed that they did not know how many free tickets were available, but they were not offered to all council staff.<ref name=\"council\">{{cite web|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/2011/10/08/cardiff-left-star-struck-by-jackson-gig-performers-91466-29559243/#ixzz1raouWyqW |title= Cardiff left star struck by Jackson gig performers|publisher= [[CardiffOnline]] |accessdate=10 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Support==\nThe event was organised by Global Live Events and had the support of Jackson's mother [[Katherine Jackson]],<ref name=\"tickets\"/> his sister [[La Toya Jackson|La Toya]] and his brothers [[Tito Jackson|Tito]], [[Marlon Jackson|Marlon]] and [[Jackie Jackson|Jackie]], but not that of his other brothers [[Randy Jackson|Randy]] and [[Jermaine Jackson|Jermaine]], his other sister [[Janet Jackson|Janet]], several relatives, the official Michael Jackson Fan Club or even the singer's executors, as they claimed the concert would distract from the involuntary manslaughter trial of Dr. [[Conrad Murray]], Jackson's former doctor. Randy and Jermaine issued the following statement in opposition to the event:\n\n<blockquote>While we wholeheartedly support the spirit of a tribute that honours our brother, we find it impossible to support an event that is due to take place during the criminal trial surrounding Michael's death. As everyone knows, those proceedings commence 20 September, and this Michael Forever concert takes place in Cardiff, Wales, on 8 October. In light of this, we feel it is inappropriate to be involved with such an ill-timed event and its promoter, Global Live. Furthermore, the decision to proceed with this concert disrespects opinions and wishes expressed in the strongest terms to Global Live during conversations in April when this event was presented to the majority of the family as an idea already in its advanced stages. There will come a time and place for an amazing and deserving tribute to Michael. But we feel that the most important tribute we can give to our brother at this time is to seek justice in his name.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-south-east-wales-14287845 |publisher= [[BBC]] |title= Michael Jackson Cardiff show: Brothers criticise timing|accessdate=7 August 2011 |date=26 July 2011}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nThe Michael Jackson Fan Club agreed with the two brothers, issuing a similar statement:\n\n<blockquote>\"We share their concerns that this concert is taking place at a most inappropriate time when everyone's care and attention should be focused on the matter of justice. We believe that, as stated by Jermaine and Randy, the most important tribute we can give to Michael Jackson at this time is to seek justice in his name.\"<ref name=\"MJFC\">{{cite web |url= http://mjfanclub.net/home/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4721:statement-from-mjfc&catid=85:latest-news&Itemid=82 |publisher= MJFC |title= Statement From MJFC|accessdate=7 August 2011}}</ref>\n</blockquote>\n\n==Performing acts==\nMusical acts who participated in the event included the [[The Jacksons|Jackson Brothers]], [[Christina Aguilera]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Beyonc\u00e9]], [[Alexandra Burke]], [[Yolanda Adams]], [[3T]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Alien Ant Farm]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Cee Lo Green]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Pixie Lott]], [[Diversity (dance troupe)|Diversity]], [[Craig David]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[JLS]],<ref name=\"guardian\"/> [[Ne-Yo]], [[Jamie Foxx]], [[Gladys Knight]], [[La Toya Jackson]], [[Leona Lewis]]<ref name=\"BBC1\"/> and [[Smokey Robinson]].<ref name=\"BBC1\"/> The [[BBC Radio 1]] presenter [[Fearne Cotton]] co-hosted the event with [[Jamie Foxx]].<ref name=\"Hunt\"/>\n\nIn the days running up to the event, three of the acts originally booked to perform pulled out: [[The Black Eyed Peas]], due to \"unforeseeable circumstances\", which led to speculation in the media that the band were splitting up; [[Chris Brown]], who failed to enter the country for the event as his working visa was denied over the assault of former girlfriend [[Rihanna]]; and [[Jennifer Hudson]], due to \"production issues\". [[Kiss (band)|KISS]] was also removed from the lineup after bass guitarist Gene Simmons made some hurtful comments against Jackson based on the child molestation allegations.\n\n===Setlist===\n\n# [[Billie Jean]]\n# [[The Lady in My Life]] - [[Ne-Yo]]\n# [[The Way You Make Me Feel]] - [[JLS]]\n# [[Blame It on the Boogie]] - JLS & The Jacksons\n# [[Shake Your Body (Down to the Ground)]] - [[The Jacksons]]\n# [[Rock with You]] - [[Jamie Foxx]]\n# [[Smooth Criminal]]\n# [[P.Y.T. (Pretty Young Thing)]] - [[Alien Ant Farm]]\n# [[Stranger in Moscow]]\n# [[I'll Be There (The Jackson 5 song)|I'll Be There]] - [[Leona Lewis]]\n# [[Human Nature (Michael Jackson song)|Human Nature]] - [[Craig David]]\n# [[Can You Feel It (The Jacksons song)|Can You Feel It]]/[[Show You the Way to Go]]/[[Smooth Criminal]]/[[Dangerous (Michael Jackson album)|Dangerous]]/[[Thriller (Michael Jackson album)|Thriller]] - Dance Jam\n# [[She's Out of My Life]] - [[Smokey Robinson]]\n# Believe in Yourself - [[Gladys Knight]]\n# [[I Wanna Be Where You Are]] - [[Beyonc\u00e9]] (On Video Screen)\n# [[I Just Can't Stop Loving You]] - Gladys Knight & Smokey Robinson\n# [[Why (3T song)|Why]]/[[Heartbreak Hotel]] - 3T & [[Tito Jackson]]\n# [[Jam (song)|Jam]]/[[Black or White]]/[[Remember the Time]]/[[Behind the Mask (Michael Jackson song)|Behind the Mask]] - [[Diversity (dance troupe)|Diversity]]\n# [[In the Closet]]/[[Jam (song)|Jam]] - [[La Toya Jackson]]\n# [[I Can't Help It (Michael Jackson song)|I Can't Help It]]\n# [[You Can't Win (song)|You Can't Win]] - [[Cee Lo Green]]\n# Smile\n# [[Dirty Diana]] - [[Christina Aguilera]]\n# [[I Want You Back]]\n# [[You Are Not Alone]] - [[Pixie Lott]]\n# [[Earth Song]] \n# [[Another Part of Me]] - [[Yolanda Adams]]\n# [[Who's Loving You]]\n# [[Scream/Childhood|Scream]] - [[Alexandra Burke]]\n# [[Leave Me Alone (Michael Jackson song)|Leave Me Alone]]\n# [[Gone Too Soon]] - [[Jennifer Hudson]]\n# [[Don't Stop 'Til You Get Enough]] - Jamie Foxx, JLS & The Jacksons\n\n==Aftermath of the event==\nGlobal Live Events LLP, which had been formed on 29 March 2011 by film producers Michael Henry and Chris Hunt went into [[Administration (law)|administration]] on the day of the concert, when both Henry and Hunt both quit the partnership.<ref name=Administration>{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/nov/29/michael-jackson-tribute-concert-company-bust|publisher= [[guardian.co.uk]]|title= Michael Jackson tribute concert company goes bust|accessdate=27 December 2011|location=London|first=Sean|last=Michaels|date=29 November 2011}}</ref>\nBoth men, Global Live Events and Hunt's media company Iambic Productions were sued in the High Court by Quickdraw - a private investment fund, over ownership of the recordings of the concert. Quickdraw won the case, with the judge stating that Hunt and Henry were 'the most unreliable of witnesses' and their account to the court was 'wholly unbelievable'. Quickdraw was awarded damages of \u00a35 million and costs of in excess of \u00a3700,000\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of music concerts at the Millennium Stadium]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20111029153612/http://home.michaelforevertribute.com/home.html Official website]\n* [http://www.facebook.com/M4Tribute Official Facebook Page]\n* [https://twitter.com/M4Tribute Official Twitter Page]\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-14289473 Video of Concert Ann