ess which item is lying on a table situated in a room two floors above him. This sample is taken from a Moscow radio broadcast translation. A near translation into English is:\n<blockquote>\nThis is either a metal or... If it is a metal, then it's painted... Cold surface... This is either a metal, painted, or could be a plastic... Colorful, there are... Bright... Seems like... Is this a toy? Probably. The surface is smooth, but... There are some bumps on it... Even the finger sticks in it... Probably it is... Some marks, or are these letters?... Or just bumps... Looks like a toy... Colorful metal, or a plastic... Painted metal... That's all... Stop.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Biosphere-Substrata/release/15775|title=Biosphere - Substrata|website=Discogs|accessdate=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n</blockquote>\n\n==In popular culture==\nThe track \"Antennaria\" was used in the 2009 video game ''[[Osmos]]''.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Man with a Movie Camera (The Cinematic Orchestra album)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Discogs master|23402|Substrata}}\n\n{{Biosphere}}\n\n[[Category:1997 albums]]\n[[Category:Biosphere (musician) albums]]\n[[Category:All Saints Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "Holiday56", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReception", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Substrata_(album)"}
{"title_page": "2020 Coronavirus pandemic in Jharkhand", "text_new": "{{Infobox pandemic\n| width           = \n|image=Special Hospital for Corona patients 1.jpg\n| name            = \n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| map4            = \n| legend4         = \n| map5            = \n| legend5         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Jharkhand]], [[India]]\n| first_case      = [[Ranchi]]\n| arrival_date    = 31 March 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=31|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = \n| confirmed_cases = 45\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 4\n| deaths          = 2\n| territories     = 6 districts: [[Ranchi district|Ranchi]], [[Bokaro district|Bokaro]], [[Hazaribagh district|Hazaribagh]], [[Dhanbad district|Dhanbad]], [[Simdega district|Simdega]], [[Deoghar district|Deoghar]]\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n| youtube         = \n}}\nThe first case of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed in the Indian state of [[Jharkhand]] on 31 March 2020 as a Malaysian women came positive on the test.<ref>https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-pandemic-malaysian-woman-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-first-case-in-jharkhand-2203922</ref> The state has confirmed a total of 45 cases, including 2 death and 4 recoveries, as of 21 April 2020. <ref>https://www.livemint.com/news/india/4-new-coronavirus-cases-reported-in-jharkhand-as-of-8-00-am-apr-21-11587438365911.html</ref>\n\n==Testing and Treatment Measures==\n[[Chaibasa]] district headquarters of [[West Singhbhum]] launched coronavirus swab collection booth which is India's first of the kind. <ref>https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/covid-19-sample-collection-mobile-booth-becomes-operational-in-chaibasa/story-choyHmTaNnbiAfQeTbtMTM.html</ref> [[Chaibasa]] also launched remote-controlled robot called co-bot for providing medicines and food and minimize the contact between the staff and the patients. <ref>https://www.latestly.com/india/news/remote-controlled-robot-co-bot-developed-in-jharkhands-chaibasa-to-provide-food-medicine-to-covid-19-patients-1686057.html</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:right; font-size:90%; width:400px;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |District\n! scope=\"col\" |Total cases\n! scope=\"col\" |Recovered\n! scope=\"col\" |Deaths\n! scope=\"col\" |Notes\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |[[Ranchi district|Ranchi]]\n| 25\n| \n| 1\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |[[Bokaro district|Bokaro]]\n| 10\n| \n| 1\n|\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" |[[Hazaribagh district|Hazaribagh]]\n| 3\n| \n| \n|\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" |[[Dhanbad district|Dhanbad]]\n| 2\n| \n| \n|\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" |[[Simdega district|Simdega]]\n| 2\n| \n| \n|\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" |[[Deoghar district|Deoghar]]\n| 1\n| \n| \n|\n|- \n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Total (all districts)\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" | 45\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" | 4\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" | 2\n!\n|- class=\"sortbottom\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"5\" |<small>As of 21 April 2020.<br>Source: [https://www.jagran.com/jharkhand/ranchi-bokaro-jharkhand-coronavirus-cases-news-update-bokaro-man-test-coronavirus-positive-today-total-42-corona-positive-in-jharkhand-coronavirus-latest-news-coronavirus-update-20207810.html] and news reports</small>\n|}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox pandemic\n| width           = \n|image=Special Hospital for Corona patients 1.jpg\n| name            = \n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| map4            = \n| legend4         = \n| map5            = \n| legend5         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Jharkhand]], [[India]]\n| first_case      = [[Ranchi]]\n| arrival_date    = 31 March 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=31|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = \n| confirmed_cases = 45\n| suspected_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 4\n| deaths          = 2\n| territories     = 6 districts: [[Ranchi district|Ranchi]], [[Bokaro district|Bokaro]], [[Hazaribagh district|Hazaribagh]], [[Dhanbad district|Dhanbad]], [[Simdega district|Simdega]], [[Deoghar district|Deoghar]]\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n| youtube         = \n}}\nThe first case of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed in the Indian state of [[Jharkhand]] on 31 March 2020 as a Malaysian women came positive on the test.<ref>https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-pandemic-malaysian-woman-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-first-case-in-jharkhand-2203922</ref> The state has confirmed a total of 45 cases, including 2 death and 4 recoveries, as of 21 April 2020. <ref>https://www.livemint.com/news/india/4-new-coronavirus-cases-reported-in-jharkhand-as-of-8-00-am-apr-21-11587438365911.html</ref>\n\n==Testing and Treatment Measures==\n[[Chaibasa]] district headquarters of [[West Singhbhum]] launched coronavirus swab collection booth which is India's first of the kind. <ref>https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/covid-19-sample-collection-mobile-booth-becomes-operational-in-chaibasa/story-choyHmTaNnbiAfQeTbtMTM.html</ref> [[Chaibas]] also launched remote-controlled robot called co-bot for providing medicines and food and minimize the contact between the staff and the patients. <ref>https://www.latestly.com/india/news/remote-controlled-robot-co-bot-developed-in-jharkhands-chaibasa-to-provide-food-medicine-to-covid-19-patients-1686057.html</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:right; font-size:90%; width:400px;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |District\n! scope=\"col\" |Total cases\n! scope=\"col\" |Recovered\n! scope=\"col\" |Deaths\n! scope=\"col\" |Notes\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |[[Ranchi district|Ranchi]]\n| 25\n| \n| 1\n|\n|